Privacy Policy

Thank you for using our Signature App "QuickSign". This Privacy Policy is here to help you understand what information we collect, why we collect it, and how we use it.

By using the App, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.

No Data Collection

The App does not collect, store, or transmit any personal information or data from users. We do not require users to provide any personal information to use the App. Additionally, the App operates entirely offline, meaning it does not communicate with any external servers or services.

Usage of Images

The App allows users to create and save signature images locally on their device's gallery. These images are solely stored on the user's device and are not accessible to the App or any third parties.

Permissions

The App may require certain permissions to access device storage in order to save signature images to the gallery. These permissions are strictly used for the intended functionality of the App and are not used for any other purpose.

No Third-party Services

The App does not contain any third-party services, plugins, or links to external websites. Users can rest assured that their data remains within the confines of their own device.

Security

We prioritize the security and privacy of our users' data. The App is designed to ensure that user-generated content, such as signature images, remains secure and private on the user's device.

Updates to Privacy Policy

Any updates to this Privacy Policy will be communicated within the App. Users are encouraged to review the Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.

Contact Us

If you have any questions or concerns about our Privacy Policy or the App's functionality, please contact us at Nabeelshahzad88@gmail.com.

By using the App, you agree to the terms outlined in this Privacy Policy.

